# Podium AI — AI Speech Coaching Platform

Two products in one app:

1. **Voice Coach** (`/voice-coach`) — Real-time spoken practice via ElevenLabs Conversational AI. Modes: Interview, Debate, Presentation, Impromptu Speaking.
2. **Speech Evaluator** (`/speech-eval`) — Timed speech on a topic; three AI judges (Rex/Counter, Clara/Grammarian, Marcus/Evaluator) with scored feedback and TTS playback.

Authenticated users get a **dashboard** (`/dashboard`) with history, stats, and voice-coach homework.

---

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js App Router (`app/`) — never `pages/`
- **Language:** TypeScript only (`.ts` / `.tsx`)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `globals.css`) — utility classes only; no extra `.css` files; no inline `style=`
- **Auth & DB:** Supabase Auth + Postgres (`@supabase/ssr`, `@supabase/supabase-js`)
- **LLM:** OpenAI GPT-4o via `getOpenAI()` / `@/lib/openai` — Groq `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` only in `catch` fallbacks via `getGroq()`
- **Voice:** ElevenLabs STT/TTS + Conversational AI (`@elevenlabs/react` on Voice Coach UI only)
- **Icons:** `lucide-react`
- **Deploy:** Vercel — keep `npm run build` passing

No model picker in the UI. GPT-4o is default; Groq is silent fallback.

