## Security — never break these

- **Server-only secrets:** `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GROQ_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_VOICE_COACH_AGENT_ID`
  - Use only in `app/api/**`, `lib/**` server modules, and Route Handlers
  - Never in client components, never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`, never `console.log` keys/tokens
- **Client-safe:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` (anon key is public by design; RLS enforces row access)
- **Auth:** Use `supabase.auth.getUser()` — not `getSession()` — for security-sensitive checks
- **Protected routes:** `app/(protected)/**` uses `requireUser()` in layout; API routes that need login call `requireUser()` too
- **Validate** every request body / FormData field before use; cap uploads via `@/lib/api-guards` (`MAX_AUDIO_BYTES`, `MAX_SPEAK_TEXT_LENGTH`, rate limits)
- **try/catch** all external API calls; return JSON errors with correct HTTP status; log with `[route-name]` prefix
- Never hardcode secrets; never commit `.env.local`

