## App Structure (unified codebase)

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Public landing | `app/page.tsx`, `components/landing/**` |
| Auth | `app/login`, `app/signup`, `app/auth/callback`, `components/auth/**` |
| Protected app | `app/(protected)/**` — dashboard, voice-coach, speech-eval |
| API | `app/api/**` |
| Shared logic | `lib/**` |
| Dashboard UI | `components/dashboard/**` |
| Voice Coach UI | `components/voice-coach/**` |
| Session middleware | `middleware.ts` (Supabase cookie refresh) |

Persistence details: `docs/supabase-persistence.md`. Run migrations in `supabase/migrations/` before expecting DB features.

Prefer small, focused changes in the right folder — no separate “subteam” ownership; coordinate on shared `lib/`, `app/layout.tsx`, and dashboard when behavior crosses features.

---

## Shared Clients — import, do not reinitialize

```typescript
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'   // Route Handlers & Server Components
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client'  // Client Components only
import { getOpenAI } from '@/lib/openai'
import { getGroq } from '@/lib/groq'
```

Use `readEnv()` from `@/lib/elevenlabs-config` for ElevenLabs env vars (handles quoted values).

---

## Hard Rules

- No OpenAI / Groq / ElevenLabs API calls from client components — use `app/api/*` (Voice Coach may use `@elevenlabs/react` with **signed URLs** from the server, not raw API keys)
- No `any` without a short comment why
- No empty `catch` — log and return a proper response
- No committed `TODO`s in finished work
- Do not redesign existing UI unless asked
- New npm packages only when necessary and agreed

---

## Git

- Never commit directly to `dev` or `main`
- Branch: `feature/yourname-description`
- Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `style:`, `chore:`
- PR into `dev` when a chunk works end-to-end
- `git pull origin dev` before new work
